# LT-94698: Riso | Core | Subject in Lesson Detail

ID: https://manabie.atlassian.net/browse/LT-94698

## Summary

Riso requires subject information linked to each lesson for auditing and reporting purposes (instructor matching, personalized curricula, instructional records). This feature adds a Subject field (Subject Master lookup) to lessons — optional, single-select. The field must be visible and editable on SF, BO, Calendar, and Learning App, and support CSV import, search, and filter.

## Acceptance Criteria

### AC 01 — Specify Subject on Lesson

- **AC 01.1** Allow the user to specify the Subject (Subject Master lookup) of each lesson.
- **AC 01.2** Lesson's Subject is optional.
- **AC 01.3** Single select (only one subject per lesson).

### AC 02 — CSV Import

- **AC 02.1** Allow the user to specify the subject through bulk CSV import.

### AC 03 — Display Subject

- **AC 03.1** Display the lesson's Subject in SF – Lesson Details (above Location).
- **AC 03.2** Display the lesson's Subject in SF – Calendar – Lesson Info.
- **AC 03.3** Display the lesson's Subject in BO – Lesson Details (above Location).
- **AC 03.4** Display the lesson's Subject in BO – Calendar – Lesson Info.
- **AC 03.5** Display the lesson's Subject in Mobile – Learning App.

### AC 04 — Search by Subject

- **AC 04.1** SF Lessons — Search for Subject (do not add Subject to list columns as core; just confirm it can be shown and searching works).
- **AC 04.2** BO – Lesson Management — Search by Subject.

### AC 05 — Filter by Subject

- **AC 05.1** SF Calendar — Filter by Subject.
- **AC 05.2** BO Calendar — Filter by Subject.
- **AC 05.3** BO – Lesson Management — Subject Filter (confirm cross-field validation).

### AC 06 — Exclusions and Constraints

- **AC 06.1** Aver custom page will NOT have this field.
- **AC 06.2** No teacher-subject validation (eligible_subject) is required.
- **AC 06.3** No course-subject relationship is required.

